<hr>
<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body 
of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	&#34;Title of episode (if appropriate).&#34; Name(s) particular to episode (if appropriate). 
	<em>Title of Work</em>. Name(s) particular to the work. Name of network (publisher). 
	Date of broadcast. Medium of broadcast.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of episode (if appropriate)">Six of One</span>.&#34; 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) particular to episode (if appropriate)">Auth. Michael Angeli. Dir. Anthony Hemingway</span>. 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Work">Battlestar Galactica</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) particular to the work">Prod. Ronald D. Moore</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name of network (publisher)">Sci Fi Channel</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Date of broadcast">11 Apr. 2008</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Medium of broadcast">Television</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are citing a particular performer, include that person&#8217;s name before the title of 
episode/work.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Name of performer">Walters, Julie M. perf.</span> 
	&#34;<span class="hover" title="Title of episode (if appropriate)">Episode 3</span>.&#34; 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Work">The Secret Diary of Adrian Mole Aged 13 3/4</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name(s) particular to the work">By Sue Townsend. Prod. Peter Sasdy</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Name of network (publisher)">Thames Television</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="Date of broadcast">30 Sept. 1985</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Medium of broadcast">Television</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
